Hello Everyone,
I did have problem in my wisdom teeth, and it has to be extracted. Dr. Sushan Sharma had explained the procedure before extraction, and He was talking while performing the procedure which made me feel relaxed. I am posting this little bit late, as I wanna tell my complete experience from extraction to recovery. The extraction was done on 16 June 2022, and I felt OK as local anesthesia was given. For the next 2 days I took only ice creams and fruit juices, and started taking mild food thereafter. Usually most of the people gets their face inflammation after tooth extraction, but I didn’t get any inflammation (may be due to my personal immunity). Sutures had been removed on 24 June 2022, doctor said there’s no infection. Due to tooth removal a hole will be formed which will take 30-45 days for complete sealing. So, it’s been 3 weeks and I feel no pain at all, but I am taking complete care so that food particles will not go in the hole.
I had a better experience with the hospital (Kirpa Dental, West Patel Nagar), and the doctor (Dr. Sushan Sharma). Thank you doc, I feel better now…
Thank you all…
